{
  "local_port": 32864,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are some recipes using 4 ounces of steak?",
  "response": "Certainly! A 4-ounce steak can be the perfect portion for a single serving or part of a larger meal. Here are several delicious recipes that make the most of a tender 4-ounce cut of steak:\n\n---\n\n### 1. **Classic Steak Salad**\n\n**Ingredients:**\n- 4 oz steak (such as sirloin or flank)\n- Salt and pepper, to taste\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 4 cups mixed salad greens\n- \u00bd cup cherry tomatoes, halved\n- \u00bc red onion, thinly sliced\n- \u00bc cucumber, sliced\n- 2 tablespoons crumbled feta or blue cheese\n- Your favorite vinaigrette dressing\n\n**Instructions:**\n1. **Prepare the Steak:**\n   - Season the steak generously with salt and pepper on both sides.\n   - Heat the olive oil in a skillet over medium-high heat.\n   - Cook the steak for about 3-4 minutes per side for medium-rare, or until desired doneness.\n   - Remove from heat and let it rest for 5 minutes before slicing thinly against the grain.\n\n2. **Assemble the Salad:**\n   - In a large bowl, combine the mixed greens, cherry tomatoes, red onion, and cucumber.\n   - Top with the sliced steak and sprinkle with feta or blue cheese.\n   - Drizzle with your favorite vinaigrette dressing and toss gently to combine.\n\n3. **Serve:**\n   - Serve immediately as a hearty and nutritious meal.\n\n---\n\n### 2. **Steak Tacos**\n\n**Ingredients:**\n- 4 oz steak (flank or skirt steak works well)\n- 1 teaspoon chili powder\n- \u00bd teaspoon cumin\n- \u00bd teaspoon garlic powder\n- Salt and pepper, to taste\n- 1 tablespoon vegetable oil\n- 2 small corn or flour tortillas\n- Toppings:\n  - Diced onions\n  - Chopped cilantro\n  - Lime wedges\n  - Salsa or pico de gallo\n  - Avocado or guacamole\n\n**Instructions:**\n1. **Season the Steak:**\n   - In a small bowl, combine chili powder, cumin, garlic powder, salt, and pepper.\n   - Rub the seasoning mixture all over the steak.\n\n2. **Cook the Steak:**\n   - Heat vegetable oil in a skillet over medium-high heat.\n   - Add the steak and cook for about 4-5 minutes per side for medium-rare.\n   - Remove from heat and let it rest for a few minutes before slicing into thin strips.\n\n3. **Warm the Tortillas:**\n   - Heat the tortillas in a dry skillet or microwave until warm and pliable.\n\n4. **Assemble the Tacos:**\n   - Place slices of steak onto each tortilla.\n   - Top with diced onions, chopped cilantro, a squeeze of lime, salsa, and avocado or guacamole.\n\n5. **Serve:**\n   - Enjoy your flavorful and customizable steak tacos!\n\n---\n\n### 3. **Beef Stir-Fry**\n\n**Ingredients:**\n- 4 oz steak (such as sirloin), thinly sliced against the grain\n- 1 tablespoon soy sauce\n- 1 teaspoon cornstarch\n- 1 tablespoon vegetable oil\n- 1 cup mixed vegetables (e.g., bell peppers, broccoli, snap peas, carrots)\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 teaspoon fresh ginger, grated\n- 2 tablespoons oyster sauce or additional soy sauce\n- 1 teaspoon sesame oil (optional)\n- Cooked rice or noodles, for serving\n\n**Instructions:**\n1. **Marinate the Beef:**\n   - In a bowl, combine the sliced steak with soy sauce and cornstarch. Mix well and let it sit for about 10 minutes.\n\n2. **Cook the Beef:**\n   - Heat vegetable oil in a large skillet or wok over high heat.\n   - Add the marinated beef and stir-fry until browned, about 2-3 minutes. Remove from the skillet and set aside.\n\n3. **Stir-Fry the Vegetables:**\n   - In the same skillet, add a bit more oil if needed.\n   - Add the mixed vegetables and stir-fry for about 4-5 minutes until tender-crisp.\n   - Add the minced garlic and grated ginger, cooking for another 30 seconds until fragrant.\n\n4. **Combine and Season:**\n   - Return the beef to the skillet.\n   - Add oyster sauce and sesame oil, stirring to combine everything thoroughly.\n   - Cook for an additional 1-2 minutes until everything is heated through.\n\n5. **Serve:**\n   - Serve the beef stir-fry over cooked rice or noodles for a satisfying meal.\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Steak Sandwich with Caramelized Onions**\n\n**Ingredients:**\n- 4 oz steak (ribeye or top sirloin)\n- Salt and pepper, to taste\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 small onion, thinly sliced\n- 1 teaspoon balsamic vinegar\n- 1 clove garlic, minced\n- 2 slices of your favorite bread or baguette\n- 1 tablespoon butter\n- 1 slice cheese (cheddar, provolone, or your choice)\n- Optional toppings: arugula, horseradish sauce, or mustard\n\n**Instructions:**\n1. **Cook the Steak:**\n   - Season the steak with salt and pepper.\n   - Heat olive oil in a skillet over medium-high heat.\n   - Cook the steak for about 3-4 minutes per side for medium-rare.\n   - Remove from heat, let it rest for 5 minutes, then slice thinly.\n\n2. **Caramelize the Onions:**\n   - In the same skillet, add a little more oil if needed.\n   - Add the sliced onions and cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until they begin to soften.\n   - Add the balsamic vinegar and continue to cook until the onions are golden and caramelized, about 15-20 minutes.\n   - Add the minced garlic in the last minute of cooking.\n\n3. **Prepare the Bread:**\n   - Butter one side of each bread slice.\n   - Place one slice, buttered side down, on a skillet over medium heat.\n   - Add the cheese slice on top to melt slightly.\n   - Layer the sliced steak and caramelized onions on top of the cheese.\n   - Add any additional toppings if desired.\n   - Top with the second bread slice, buttered side up.\n   - Grill until the bread is golden brown and the cheese is melted, flipping once.\n\n4. **Serve:**\n   - Slice the sandwich in half and enjoy a hearty and flavorful meal.\n\n---\n\nThese recipes are versatile and can be adjusted based on your preferences and what ingredients you have on hand. Enjoy cooking with your 4-ounce steak!",
